+### Codex
+
+`repowise init` offers Codex setup in interactive runs when `codex --version` and `codex login status` succeed. Non-interactive runs require `--codex`. You can force or skip it:
+
+```bash
+repowise init --codex
+repowise init --no-codex
+```
+
+Generated project-local files:
+
+```text
+.codex/config.toml
+.codex/hooks.json
+AGENTS.md
+```
+
+The Codex MCP config uses no-path mode:
+
+```toml
+[mcp_servers.repowise]
+command = "repowise"
+args = ["mcp"]
+cwd = "/path/to/your-repo"
+startup_timeout_sec = 20
+```
+
+In no-path mode, `repowise mcp` walks upward to the nearest initialized `.repowise` repository. Verify the setup with:
+
+```bash
+codex mcp list
+```
